title: "Aura: An On-Device Empathetic Intelligence Layer for Indian Gen Z"
message: "If you reference Aura in academic or technical work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-05-07"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/ShAuRyA-Noodle/Combobulating"
url: "https://shaurya-noodle.github.io/Combobulating"
abstract: >-
  Aura is a multi-agent on-device empathetic intelligence layer for Indian
  Gen Z and Gen Alpha smartphone users. Four specialist agents — Communications,
  Calendar, Finance, Wellness — are coordinated by a Phi-3-mini orchestrator
  running on a deterministic seven-state LangGraph state machine. Every action
  emits a glass-box Reasoning Trace. A daily Silence Budget caps proactive
  surfaces at three per local day. A user-owned, encrypted SQLite memory graph
  with a hash-chained audit log persists context on-device. Built for the
  Samsung EnnovateX 2026 hackathon by a two-person undergraduate team on a
  total budget of ₹2,000.
